The PCE, defined as the fraction of incident optical power Popt that is converted into electricity with output power Pel, is the most important parameter describing a photovoltaic device. It is given by the product of open-circuit voltage VOC, short-circuit current ISC, and fill factor FF:1PCE=PelPopt=VOCISCFFPopt.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
